programme.title: Storage Wars S12E268 ?
programme.desc: Mary's transportation troubles lead to teaming up with Kenny. Darrell shows the next generation how it's done. The Vegas Ladies' mid-century style lets them write their own ticket.

programme.title: Pawn Stars S19E490
programme.desc: Chumlee pays a huge sum to have an antique headlamp tester shining brightly once again. Corey and Chumlee take a stab at buying a prop from the classic horror movie 'Child's Play'.

programme.title: Pawn Stars S19E492
programme.desc: Rick and Chumlee come to grips with a valuable Japanese katana from the 1800s; Rick assesses a set of sea turtle coins from the ancient Mediterranean city of Aegina.

programme.desc: Fathers know best when it comes to picking. Mike and Frank meet up with fellow picking families.

programme.title: Chasing Monsters S2E7
programme.desc: Cyril travels to a remote and dangerous environment in Uganda on the hunt for the largest freshwater fish in Africa, the Nile perch, a massive beast with a cavernous mouth that can swallow big prey.

programme.title: Swamp People S10E7
programme.desc: As a major storm rages in the Gulf Coast, Troy, Terral, Jacob and Dusty race to run their lines before the storm sinks their gators.

programme.title: Swamp People S10E8
programme.desc: Ronnie wins extra tags in a poker game that he and Ashley are eager to fill and cash in. Troy plans a nocturnal stakeout to catch the mysterious man poaching his lines.

programme.title: Mountain Men S8E108
programme.desc: Jake will do anything to get his injured dog, Lefty, to the vet. Tom and his brother, Jack, are left high and dry when the well on his ranch stops pumping.

programme.title: Swamp Mysteries With Troy Landry S1E4
programme.desc: Troy embarks on a mission to protect locals from an unknown beast lurking in Louisiana's most mysterious bayou.

programme.title: Alone S6E4
programme.desc: The survivalists get serious about hunting before the wildlife starts to disappear for the winter. One participant has a chance to make Alone history, while another is set back by a puncture wound.

programme.title: The Pickers S13E34
programme.desc: In this Best Of episode, Mike's passion for all things automotive is explored with a selection of the best garage-related moments.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E7
programme.desc: Thorn goes on a nutria hunt hoping to provide protein that Delia and he need to survive, Tony and Amelia take a big step in their homesteading journey and attempt to sell goods at market in town, Colbert is in the midst of a natural disaster as rising waters put his new cabin construction at risk, and Matt goes on a turkey hunt in the canyons he now calls home.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E3
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz have taken on a famous German roadster from the 60s, a Mercedes 230SL. The car belongs to petrol head John who bought it as a restoration project. Unfortunately when John suffered a heart attack the task of getting the Mercedes was too much and the iconic was left abandoned. Now Tim and Fuzz have the job of getting this aging motor back on the road but it may turn out to be the worst car they have ever picked up.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E6
programme.desc: Northern and Southern boats battle for the top-earning title, and a good price on a big fish is all that stands between them. As the seasons quota dwindles and sustainability limits are stricter, bluefin fisherman are feeling the pressure to get paid. One local boat has yet to even catch their first fish, and there is no paycheck without a bluefin on deck.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E6
programme.desc: Actor-musician Jack Black and his Tenacious D bandmate Kyle Gass join Keegan-Michael Key to learn how music affects the brain. Games and demonstrations include a round of musical mad libs, 'Odd-itory' illusions and experiments that show how music can affect our perception of images, emotions and even taste. Master mentalist Lior Suchard asks Black to think of any song in the world and tries to guess it correctly. Black tests his brain power in the Gauntlet, and afterward he is joined by singer-songwriter Meghan Trainor for an improvised onstage jam session.

programme.title: Mega Breakdown S2E1
programme.desc: Experts mobilize to demolish a 25,000-ton dam built of concrete and steel. They turn the energy of a perfect storm against the debris. With a century's worth of rocks and sand stacked up against it, they need a radical, dangerous plan.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E11
programme.desc: Thailand beckons, and Greer teams up with her friend and guide, Rhi, to discover as much as she can about his beautiful Thai island in 48 hours. In among all the water fun like whitewater rafting and snorkelling, Rhi makes sure Greer has time for the absolute must-do – a Thai cooking course. Yum!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E12
programme.desc: Greer is California dreaming in San Francisco on a 48-hour trip that mixes nature with eclectic neighbourhoods, plus a boat ride under the Golden Gate Bridge. Consultant Kelly is her guide as they criss-cross the Bay area from Napa Valley wineries to towering redwood forests and from hippie haunts to modern art.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E11
programme.desc: The Outer Banks Bluefin quota is filling up fast and with the legal limit for catching them at one fish a day, the competition is getting fierce. Northern and Southern fleets are determined to do whatever it takes to get paydays for their crews but when one captain loses his mate, a dangerous game ensues. Only the strong survive but who has what it takes in the battle between man and nature?

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S9E1
programme.desc: Hear the stories of Sen. John McCain and Ernest Brace, pilots who were imprisoned in Vietnam during the war. Sen. McCain was a U.S. Navy pilot who was forced to eject over Hanoi and was caught after landing in a lake, while Brace was a civilian pilot who ended up being the longest-serving civilian prisoner of the Vietnam War.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E5
programme.desc: Tom Hanway takes a trip to South America with a plan to trade 500 hits of LSD for a kilo of cocaine and smuggle it back into California but the deal goes awry. Arrested and sentenced to five years in a Chilean prison, Tom decides to escape with fellow inmate, Chosco. Once out, the pair flees the country on foot, embarking on a fatal journey through the desert with the police in hot pursuit.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E4
programme.desc: Historian Sam Willis is on a journey around China to trace the origins of food. From 7000-year-old rice grains to 4000-year-old noodles and a 2000-year-old irrigation system that's still in use, he discovers how the quest to feed its people has shaped the nation over millennia, and how the same challenges are being met in the nation today.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E1
programme.desc: Hidden in the remote mountains, almost 16,000ft above sea level, China's most tenacious wildlife face daily battles to survive. Follow a fiercely determined snow leopard mother as she teaches her cub vital life lessons; watch a family of Tibetan fox face a formidable feline hunter to protect their precious young; and admire the stealth and agility of the one of the world's smallest cats.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E13
programme.desc: Greer has a right royal time experiencing all that Edinburgh has to offer. Her adventures include golf and ghosts, castles and tartans plus a walk around the famous Brittania. Local consultant Natasha has created the perfect itinerary, fit for a Queen.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E1
programme.desc: Follow host travel consultant Greer on her adventure in Queenstown. In 48 hours, she'll take in stunning scenery, enjoy exciting activities and enjoy the warm welcome of the locals. To make every minute count, local consultant Catriona, will join her and showcase the best of this beautiful destination.

programme.title: Mega Breakdown S2E2
programme.desc: The Orange Bowl home to the Miami Dolphins for 21 seasons, and host of five Super Bowls is about to be demolished. In just four months, a demolition team needs to clear over a quarter million feet of stadium to get ready for a new stadium. The iconic Orange Bowl, is about to be history.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E4
programme.desc: Oil worker Steve has owned his Aston Martin DB6 for over 20 years. After buying it for a bargain price the car became his pride and joy but when it broke down his attempts to repair the Aston failed. Since then a serious fall and chronic health problems have taken their toll and restoring the British classic is now out of his reach. While Fuzz struggles with an engine that hasn't turned over in 20 years Tim will have to do his best to get all the right Aston parts which are notoriously expensive.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E5
programme.desc: China has built some of the most impressive structures that have lasted the test of time, such as the Forbidden City and the Great Wall of China. But as the nation modernizes, so do its architectural needs and aspirations. Historian Sam Willis explores the history of Chinese architecture, the innovations and cultural considerations involved, and how it has evolved for the growing cities and future generations.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E5
programme.desc: JFK CBP stops a passenger traveling from Trinidad transporting cans of tropical fruit. But instead of fruit, the inspecting officer discovers a white powdery substance. In the Miami mail facility, CBP finds vials of a suspicious liquid which tests for GBL, a dangerous date rape drug. HSI conducts a controlled delivery hoping to arrest the smuggler. In LAX, CBP questions female passengers who might be victims of sex trafficking and marriage fraud.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E12
programme.sub-title: Coming Of Age In The Anthropocene
programme.desc: What kind of world can a child born in 2020 expect to grow up in? And when did our slide into planet-wide environmental destruction begin? The possible world that awaits our baby girl into her 20's: one darkened by our refusal to face the real and mounting challenges we face but concluding with a message of hope.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E13
programme.sub-title: Seven Wonders Of The New World
programme.desc: The young Carl Sagan and Neil Tyson first discovered their passion for science at the NY World's Fairs of the past. We visit the dazzling Pavilions of the 2039 NY World's Fair, where problems we currently think intractable have been plausibly solved through public commitment and scientific imagination. And our baby is a woman now, with a baby of her own and a future bright with possibilities.

programme.title: Is It Real? (30 Mins) E10
programme.desc: Are psychics real? Viewers are introduced to various cases where people have claimed to have made successful psychic predictions. Skeptics, however, disagree. A test is done to compare the effectiveness between cold readings, geographical profiling, and calculated guesses. A self-proclaimed psychic is also given a task to find a mother and child gone missing 28 years ago.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E7
programme.desc: The Outer Banks bluefin season is led by an unexpected Northern captain, but when the Southern fleet steps up their game even more surprises are on the horizon. Are the local fleets efforts enough to change the competition? With the quota dwindling, fishing twenty-four seven is the only option and none of the boats are backing down as the North Carolina Bluefin season heats up.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E7
programme.desc: Keegan-Michael Key welcomes billionaire CEO and star of 'Shark Tank' Mark Cuban to explore how business-savvy, powerful brains might be different from others, and how power can manipulate the way we think. Cuban and Key undergo a series of challenges involving split-second decision-making via rapid hiring and firing, memory mastery and a ruthless game of 'Simon Says.' Plus, actor Colin Hanks demonstrates the halo effect by disguising his identity to become a pretentious artist. Mentalist Lior Suchard manipulates the audience to move pendulums with their minds, and Cuban tests his mettle in the Gauntlet's mental obstacle course.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E5
programme.desc: Built in 1968, the C5 Galaxy was the biggest cargo plane EVER. With the ability to carry more cargo further than any other plane and to land anywhere, the C-5 has been a crucial part of the US Military's arsenal for almost 50 years. In this episode, Chad gets to see a C-5 being stripped down, over-hauled and rebuilt in order to serve for another 20 years. Giving him the chance to uncover the five key engineering innovations that make it King of the Skies.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E11
programme.desc: Jordan's hitting up the southwest with a stop in Tucson, Arizona. Cultures collide in this city with restaurants drawing upon southern, west coast and Mexican influences. Jordan's first stop is Pasco's, where late nite eats get a head start.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E12
programme.desc: Jordan heads to the California's bread basket, Sacramento, where the long growing season and ideal climate make the region home to all manner of amazing produce, meats and other incredible ingredients. His first stop is Hook and Ladder, a converted warehouse that serves up spectacular Italian and Mediterranean cuisine tapas style.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E12
programme.desc: Every second on the water is valuable with the Outer Banks Bluefin Season nearing an end. This year, strict limits on fishing mean boats can only bring in one fish a day and while the luckiest Northern and Southern captains battle it out for the title of top-earner, every other boat scrambles to salvage their season, snagging any Bluefin they can before it's too late.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E7
programme.desc: En route from Singapore to Perth, Qantas Airways Flight 72 takes a sudden nosedive over the Indian Ocean. Sudden G-forces are so violent passengers are lifted out of their seats. A series of over-speed and stall warnings flood the cockpit display, and it's clear something is terribly wrong. An experienced fighter pilot, the captain manages to safely land the plane. It's up to Australian investigators to uncover the mysterious and potentially deadly malfunction that's putting one of the world's most popular planes at risk.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S14E1
programme.desc: On November 19, 1996, a fiery collision between United Express 5925 and a small private plane leaves investigators stumped until they learn that a mysterious missing pilot may have played an unwitting role in the tragedy.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S4E9
programme.desc: Flight 604 crashes into the Red Sea killing all on board. Was this a terrible act of terrorism,a mechanical failure or did the crew make a mistake?

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E2
programme.desc: The Jungles of southern Yunnan are unique in China. Home to its greatest diversity of life. From primates to bears, fishing bats to bees and elephants to caterpillars, this is their story. With abundant resources life here should be easy but to survive, each must find its way to thrive. The creatures here have done exactly that through amazing adaptations some of which are filmed for the very first time.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E13
programme.desc: Jordan checks out the bay area's biggest city, Oakland, California, long known for its tremendous diversity and thriving arts and entertainment scene, and amazing Asian cuisine. His first stop is Seawolf Public House in Jack London Square, a new local where Chef Jason Moniz mashes up classic pub food with international flavours.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E1
programme.desc: Jordan checks out Toronto, Canada's most diverse city, it dishes out all kinds of delights. He kicks off his tour at Chanticler, a French style bistro located in Parkdale, an artsy enclave with a hopping late vibe.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E6
programme.desc: For forty years, Nimitz class aircraft carriers have delivered US military might wherever it is needed, anywhere on the globe. But now, this legendary design is being phased out and new carriers are planned. But until they're ready, the giant Nimitz ships have to be kept at the forefront of military technology. In this episode, engineer and host Chad Zdenek spends a week on board the USS Carl Vinson to work with the highly trained specialist engineers, mechanics and sailors who keep this incredible floating city in perfect working order during a critical mission in the Pacific - training twenty F18 pilots who have never taken off from an Aircraft Carrier before. This gives Chad the chance to discover the five engineering innovations at the heart of America's most incredible Aircraft Carrier.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E12
programme.sub-title: Coming Of Age In The Anthropocene

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E8
programme.desc: On its final approach to Zurich, Alitalia Flight 404 plows into a forested hillside killing everyone on board. Checking the DC-9's radar track, Swiss investigators immediately notice the aircraft was flying too low. But closer analysis of the evidence only deepens the mystery. Did a hidden flaw in the navigation system lead two pilots down a deadly path?

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E6
programme.desc: For forty years, Nimitz class aircraft carriers have delivered US military might wherever it is needed, anywhere on the globe. But now, this legendary design is being phased out and new carriers are planned. But until they're ready, the giant Nimitz ships have to be kept at the forefront of military technology. In this episode, engineer and host Chad Zdenek spends a week on board the USS Carl Vinson to work with the highly trained specialist engineers, mechanics and sailors who keep this incredible floating city in perfect working order during a critical mission in the Pacific - training twenty F18 pilots who have never taken off from an Aircraft Carrier before. This gives Chad the chance to discover the five engineering innovations at the heart of America's most incredible Aircraft Carrier.

programme.title: Wild Congo E2
programme.desc: Our closest relatives can be found hidden deep inside the dense jungles that surround the Congo and its feeding rivers, with three of the world's four species of great apes living in the Congo Basin. With Bonobos that use sex as a solution to conflicts and fish with long noses or gigantic trunks, the Congo has become a test laboratory of evolution and an El Dorado of biodiversity.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E1
programme.desc: Across Thailand's myriad landscapes, animals face a constant challenge - to find food. From misty rainforests to rich wetlands, salty mangrove forests to busy cities, they're locked in a deadly battle either to search out their prey or avoid becoming someone else's dinner. Their survival depends on their wits, guile and ingenuity, and losers pay the ultimate price. It's all to play for.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E2
programme.desc: In the Mating Game, creatures are pushed to the limits in the pursuit of a perfect partner and the challenge of raising a family.

programme.title: Jane
programme.desc: Using a trove of never-before-seen footage, the film tells the story of Jane's early explorations and research in Tanzania, focusing on her groundbreaking field work, her relationship with her cameraman and husband Hugo van Lawick, and the chimpanzees that were the subject of her study.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: Iran's Wild Side
programme.desc: Iran's Wild Side offers a rare look into Iran's wondrous wildlife and nature. This documentary features the marvels of this little-known land, nested in the Middle East. From the hot arid deserts and their shifting sands, to the breath-taking snow-capped mountains and their unique inhabitants, and to the lush greenery of mangroves and their unusual creatures, Iran is a land cloaked in mystery and extremes.

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side: Dynasties
programme.desc: Botswana is home to exotic and diverse creatures, but all share one single purpose: keep the bloodline alive. From finding a mate, to raising the next generation, Africa's most beloved animals fight for survival every day.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E7
programme.desc: The famed Galapagos Islands teem with fantastic wildlife. The animals that could survive the long journey and harsh climate thrived in an isolated sanctuary. But that isolation left them vulnerable to the threats of the outside world. Now the islands' guardians reveal the hidden patterns of these endangered creatures with latest technology, and gain the critical insights needed to save them.

programme.title: Wild Congo E2
programme.desc: Our closest relatives can be found hidden deep inside the dense jungles that surround the Congo and its feeding rivers, with three of the world's four species of great apes living in the Congo Basin. With Bonobos that use sex as a solution to conflicts and fish with long noses or gigantic trunks, the Congo has become a test laboratory of evolution and an El Dorado of biodiversity.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E1
programme.desc: Across Thailand's myriad landscapes, animals face a constant challenge - to find food. From misty rainforests to rich wetlands, salty mangrove forests to busy cities, they're locked in a deadly battle either to search out their prey or avoid becoming someone else's dinner. Their survival depends on their wits, guile and ingenuity, and losers pay the ultimate price. It's all to play for.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E2
programme.desc: In the Mating Game, creatures are pushed to the limits in the pursuit of a perfect partner and the challenge of raising a family.

programme.title: Japan's Wild Year
programme.desc: Japan is synonymous with crowded high tech cities. In fact around three-quarters of Japan is uninhabited forests, mountains and coast lines. Here a great diversity of wildlife ekes out an existence adapted to a country with great extremes of climate. From the tropics in the south to the sub-arctic climate of Hokkaido island. From the northernmost primates in the world, the snow monkeys, bears, giant hornets and the weird goat-antelope serow, to the iconic red-headed crane and the abundant cherry salmon, the life blood of Japanese rivers.

programme.title: Jane
programme.desc: Using a trove of never-before-seen footage, the film tells the story of Jane's early explorations and research in Tanzania, focusing on her groundbreaking field work, her relationship with her cameraman and husband Hugo van Lawick, and the chimpanzees that were the subject of her study.

programme.title: Before The Flood
programme.desc: Before the Flood captures a three-year personal journey alongside Academy Award-winning actor Leonardo DiCaprio as he interviews individuals from every facet of society around the world, including his discussions on climate change with President Obama and Pope Francis, to provide pragmatic views on what must be done today and in the future to prevent catastrophic disruption of life on our planet.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: Iran's Wild Side
programme.desc: Iran's Wild Side offers a rare look into Iran's wondrous wildlife and nature. This documentary features the marvels of this little-known land, nested in the Middle East. From the hot arid deserts and their shifting sands, to the breath-taking snow-capped mountains and their unique inhabitants, and to the lush greenery of mangroves and their unusual creatures, Iran is a land cloaked in mystery and extremes.

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side: Dynasties
programme.desc: Botswana is home to exotic and diverse creatures, but all share one single purpose: keep the bloodline alive. From finding a mate, to raising the next generation, Africa's most beloved animals fight for survival every day.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E7
programme.desc: The famed Galapagos Islands teem with fantastic wildlife. The animals that could survive the long journey and harsh climate thrived in an isolated sanctuary. But that isolation left them vulnerable to the threats of the outside world. Now the islands' guardians reveal the hidden patterns of these endangered creatures with latest technology, and gain the critical insights needed to save them.

programme.title: Photo Ark: Rarest Creatures
programme.desc: Join National Geographic photographer Joel Sartore as he travels to Madagascar, China, the Czech Republic, and New Zealand, to photograph creatures found nowhere else on the planet, and add them to his Photo Ark.

programme.title: Jane Goodall: The Hope
programme.desc: Dr, Jane Goodall arrived at a 1986 conference as a scientist and-after learning the extent of the threat facing chimpanzees-left as an activist. The film begins with this critical transformation and follows Jane through three decades of advocacy work. Jane knew she must take action to protect chimps and other animals living in the wild, to improve the well being of chimps in captivity and to inspire a young generation of change makers for this vital work to continue. In a moment in which the environmental crisis can seem overwhelming, Jane has made it her mission to encourage us all that solutions are within reach. Our cameras capture Jane as she travels over 300 days a year, meeting with everyone from schoolchildren in Zanzibar to Silicon Valley tech giants to Prince Harry, using wisdom, heart and humor to spread a message of hope and show that every individual has the potential be a catalyst and create lasting change.

programme.title: Wild Korea E2
programme.desc: The notorious demilitarized zone of Korea has existed on the boundary of two warring nations for nearly 70 years where a tense standoff still remains. However, amidst the barbed wire fences and thousands of land mines, a unique natural wonderland from wild boar to giant hornets to rare cranes peacefully co-exist alongside the ashes of war.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E4
programme.desc: Clarke enjoys a proper adventure off the East Coast of New Zealand taking a boat out to White Island, a very active volcano 50kms offhsore. Here conditions can quickly change. Catching his target fish after plenty of false alarms, Clarke takes it back to chef Josh in the local town of Whakatane. Josh specialises in celiac friendly quisine and his Hapuku dish does not dissapoint.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E3
programme.desc: According to science humans are the only mammals that are attracted to sour. Chinese medicinal believes says that ‘sour' can help digestion and whet the appetite. In traditional Chinese cuisines it is often used for balance but in south East Asian versions of Chinese dishes it is often quite forward even becoming part of the name of a dish particularly in traditional Peranakan Chinese cuisines.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E2
programme.desc: George travels to Cornwall to meet Rebecca and Damian, a young couple who are trading in their house for a debt free life in a cool, luxury American trailer known as a Silver Streak. But with just £10 grand to finish the job can they transform this trailer from trash to vintage treasure?

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E19
programme.desc: Food has always been a way to spread joy and happiness for Pablo. When he got a chance to return the favour, Pablo couldn't think of a better way than to cook for the people of North East and share the magic of food with them. Pablo talks about his most innovative dishes given the limited amount of time and unusual ingredients, he churned out some amazing recipes in the North East of India.

programme.desc: Fermentation, Alcohol & beverages: Human migration led to the spread of amazing practices in many parts of the world. People migrated with the treasure of these practices and shared them with other races. Pablo learned more about this diverse country India as he dug through the practices in North East brought by people from countries like Tibet, Burma, Laos, Vietnam.

Later, David takes a local food tour to sample all of the local Punjabi delicacies.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Island Feast E9
programme.desc: The island of Rarotonga in the Cook Islands provides Chef Peter Kuruvita with not only spectacular vistas but also unique opportunities to learn from friendly locals on how to hunt and gather native fare.

programme.title: Island Hunter E2
programme.desc: An uncommon destination for a series that explores exotic tropical getaways. But this island nation has some of the most evocative landscapes that mother nature has to offer! And, host Liesel Hlista explores the charms of the emerald state in it's off-season. Questionable weather is no match for the bounty of eats and drinks that Ireland has on offer; the best oysters this side of the Atlantic, the birthplace of Guinness and of course, the home to Irish whiskey. Liesel explores ultra luxurious (and famous) celebrity getaways like Castle Leslie, goes hands on at the Dunbrody house with celebrity chef Kevin Dundon, and explores the Wild Atlantic way at the fishing estate Ballynahinch Castle. The best way to explore Ireland in the off-season, Island Hunter style!

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E3
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets a small community of Gorlos Mongols in the northern province of Jilin who keep their culture alive through Shamanistic practices and music including a unique style called throat singing.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E4
programme.desc: The flight from Kolkata to Hong Kong was a long and exhausting one and although it's chewed into his budget, Manu can't resist the allure of a Michelin-starred restaurant in his hotel.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E5
programme.sub-title: New York: Melting Pot Of Food
programme.desc: The Statue Liberty has welcomed millions of immigrants from all over the world to New York, creating a melting pot of different cultures. We visit the big apple's vibrant neighborhoods to sample a variety of foods this great big city has to offer.

programme.title: Shandong: Land Of Confucius
programme.desc: Shandong Province is home to China's most famous philosopher- Confucius, Jonathan Clements as a historian and expert on Asian Culture, will be the host of this show. In the course of a whirlwind adventure that spans 9 carefully chosen locations throughout Shandong, Clements, a scholar of modern Asian trends gives us his fascinating take on how China got where it is today.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E2
programme.desc: John Torode is in the holy city of Amritsar in the Punjab region of northern India. His first outing takes him to the Golden Temple. What's remarkable about this site besides the temple itself is that it provides free meals to as many as 100,000 people per day, regardless of religion, colour or wealth.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E2
programme.desc: Michelle and Justin are outdoor enthusiasts and every spare moment is planned around kite surfing and paddle boarding trips. It's time for them to find their very own long beach view.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E4
programme.desc: Flying into Heathrow: an endangered parrot, and a polar vortex! Whilst Officers Dave and Terry hunt for a wanted man gone missing on a plane, Airside Ian and stickler-for-the-rules Steve battles snow in a blizzard to keep the runways open.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E3
programme.desc: Harry must assist with a medical emergency on a landing flight whilst Border Force Bob questions a circus performer from Panama. Demi saves the day again with a passenger who loses his passport.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E1
programme.desc: Jordan's in Memphis, a city known for BBQ and the Blues, but there's much more to its late night food scene. Jordan's firing up the evening with some Polynesian fare gone Southern at Atomic Tiki, a hidden tropical oasis in Overton Park. He whets his appetite with some pork belly steamed buns and gets a glimpse of their top selling favourite, the Polynesian meatballs before heading downtown.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E1
programme.desc: Matt explores what cooking with fire means to modern South Africans and discovers that it is no accident that their cuisine is so deeply attached to cooking on fire as South African DNA and the very land they live on still glows with the flames of those who cooked before them. She starts off with a quick glimpse and an impromptu jam session at the birthplace of Bob Marley, Trench town, noshes on the most delicious ice cream this side of the hemisphere, and plunges into Mystic mountain's waterfalls. Jamaica is known for being the home of the all-inclusive resort and Liesel finds out exactly why that is - with stays at Ian Fleming inspired Golden eye Hotel as well as Sunset at the Palms! Lazy tubing down the river, limestone foot massages, topped up with historic food tours and experiencing local cuisines such as jerk chicken and the amazing seafood; this is Jamaica, Island Hunter style!

programme.desc: Although Manu has visited Tokyo before, this time he is on his own and has a tight budget. Still, he is keen to learn and discover as much as he can. His first stop is the legendary fish market to learn about the renowned tuna sold there but he has to make it through the craziness of the Tokyo fish market first.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E6
programme.desc: Los Angeles is not only the center of the world's biggest film and television industry, it is also the leader in setting trends. For many years now LA has been on a health kick, making it relatively easy for people to live a healthier lifestyle. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.title: Fish of the Day S3E8
programme.desc: Clarke heads off on a South Island, NZ driving adventure. See him learning more about New Zealand's indigenous Dolphin population and the threat it faces. He also explores local waterways learning about the importance of clean local water ways to Maori before tackling wild Salmon in South Island’s famous canals.

programme.title: Miguel's Tropical Kitchen E2
programme.desc: From Green Island, one of the oldest and most beautiful Islands in the Great Barrier Reef, Miguel reveals some simple steps to a stunning Tuna Carpaccio, serves up a tropical Asian canapé and discovers some exotic tropical fruits for his delicious Sweet Fruit Wontons.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E3
programme.desc: As a lifelong lover of Chinese food, when John Torode's tour of Asian cuisine stops off in Beijing, he is understandably elated. Naturally John heads straight to a Beijing's most loved Peking Duck restaurant in the heart of the Hutongs and is fascinated to see and then taste a traditionally inflated and roasted Peking Duck.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E3
programme.desc: Wine enthusiasts Christina and Ed are ready to make their lifelong dream of having a view of a lush green vineyard come true. Their Italian and Chilean roots have led them on a quest to re-locate to wine country.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E5
programme.desc: Dairy, Drugs and Dogs headline in today's visit to Heathrow. On the airfield Airside Ian goes for promotion, whilst inside the terminals Queen of T2 Sue saves a musician from missing his concert and in security there's a serious breach.

programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. He's there to learn the secret behind their mouthwatering fried chicken, which some say is the best in the south. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.desc: Matt meets many, many cows. He learns about, admires and milks South Africa's indigenous Nguni breed in Msinga, Kwa Zulu Natal. His first stop is the legendary fish market to learn about the renowned tuna sold there but he has to make it through the craziness of the Tokyo fish market first.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E6
programme.desc: Los Angeles is not only the center of the world's biggest film and television industry, it is also the leader in setting trends. For many years now LA has been on a health kick, making it relatively easy for people to live a healthier lifestyle. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E3
programme.desc: As a lifelong lover of Chinese food, when John Torode's tour of Asian cuisine stops off in Beijing, he is understandably elated. Naturally John heads straight to a Beijing's most loved Peking Duck restaurant in the heart of the Hutongs and is fascinated to see and then taste a traditionally inflated and roasted Peking Duck.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E3
programme.desc: Wine enthusiasts Christina and Ed are ready to make their lifelong dream of having a view of a lush green vineyard come true. Their Italian and Chilean roots have led them on a quest to re-locate to wine country.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E5
programme.desc: Dairy, Drugs and Dogs headline in today's visit to Heathrow. On the airfield Airside Ian goes for promotion, whilst inside the terminals Queen of T2 Sue saves a musician from missing his concert and in security there's a serious breach.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E4
programme.desc: Flying into Heathrow: an endangered parrot, and a polar vortex! Whilst Officers Dave and Terry hunt for a wanted man gone missing on a plane, Airside Ian and stickler-for-the-rules Steve battles snow in a blizzard to keep the runways open.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E2
programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. He's there to learn the secret behind their mouthwatering fried chicken, which some say is the best in the south. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E3
programme.desc: Matt meets many, many cows. He learns about, admires and milks South Africa's indigenous Nguni breed in Msinga, Kwa Zulu Natal. Matt meets Xoliswa Ndoyiya (Nelson Mandela's personal chef) to cook the late president's favourite sour milk recipe (umphokoqo) and share memories of her time cooking for an icon.

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E2
programme.desc: There are ugly houses, and then there is Nick and Sonia's house; an appallingly designed afterthought that is essentially a flat over three dysfunctional car parking spaces. George charges award winning architects Abigail Ashton and Andrew Porter with creating something beautiful from this monstrosity. Together they have built their reputation on creating extraordinary, innovative homes in the most suburban of settings, but working with a budget of £75K can they transform this foul flat into a proper home with two floors? And what will the neighbours on their 90's estate make of the changes?

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E4
programme.desc: In addition to its world-renowned beaches and an endless supply of sunshine, San Diego is also home to a thriving art scene. From actors and chefs to architects and designers - Host and National Geographic Traveler writer, Robert Reid, discovers the limitless palette of inspiration San Diego has to offer.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E3
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison and host-model Natalie Pickles dive head in to Hakka culture by joining a Hakka Opera troupe on stage as they conclude their journey on the Taiwan Romantic Route 3. To get their performance up to scratch, our unlikely duo must first understand the basics of Hakka culture. The pair meet Professor Zheng Rom Shing to understand how Hakka opera's roots began with tea picking, before taking pronunciation lessons with a group of elementary school children. Hakka arts revolves around the environment and community.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E19
programme.desc: Food has always been a way to spread joy and happiness for Pablo. When he got a chance to return the favour, Pablo couldn't think of a better way than to cook for the people of North East and share the magic of food with them. Pablo talks about his most innovative dishes given the limited amount of time and unusual ingredients, he churned out some amazing recipes in the North East of India.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E5
programme.desc: Clarke has a good look at one of the most productive harbours in New Zealand. Home to over 20% of the world's seabird biodiversity and with a resident whale population, this unique location is an incredible harbinger of life. Clarke explores some of the harbours hidden features and shows a fishing club that has made big changes to better utilize the ocean around it.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E6
programme.desc: Chasing a Dog Tooth Tuna, Clarke encounters everything but as he tackles the waters off Apia Island, Samoa. Not that he has any complaints as he manages to hook the largest Giant Trevally he has ever captured. He also gets in the water to discover that Samoa has some incredible spearfishing in the warm clear tropical waters that surround it.

programme.desc: Clint flies in by sea plane to view the Grizzly Bears up close and also gets his hands dirty at Echo Valley Ranch in British Columbia.

Can he turn his talents to something much smaller, and will he be able to create a design that works on Martyn and Sally's budget of just £65,000?

programme.desc: Join world-renowned chef Jose Andres on an exploration of Haiti, the most unknown country in the Caribbean. Along the way Andres experiences the authentic Haiti's traditions and rituals, from making cassava bread to midnight gatherings with vodou priests, and through its unique cuisine he discovers the history and culture, and sees into the future, of a proud and rarely understood people.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E7
programme.desc: Clarke continues his adventure in Samoa. Hunting an elusive Dog Tooth tuna for Chef John, he encounters many other fish along the way including a huge Blue Marlin. programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the Island of Maui, Hawaii, to explore the secrets of Hawaiian cuisine along the rugged Hana coastline.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E6
programme.desc: After months at sea, adventurer Ellis Emmett's epic Pacific voyages lands him in the island nation of Kiribati, where he comes face-to-face with the realities of climate change, helps get a traditional sailing canoe back into the water, and befriends a king!

programme.title: Pond Stars E4
programme.desc: Greg and the team head to the sunshine state for two massive pond projects outside of Jacksonville, Florida. This first is to build one of the team's most challenging designs by completing a 30-foot pond and a 2,000-pound cypress bench. The Pond Stars then have to race the clock to design and install a new pond, patio and pergola in less than 48 hours.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S3E3
programme.desc: See some of the world's biggest animals duke it out in extreme environments across the globe. A herd of male elephants go tusk-to-tusk and trunk-to-trunk as they battle it out in the heat of the African savannah, while in frozen Alaska, two huge polar bears engage in territorial combat, leaving blood-stained snow in their wake.

programme.title: Dragon Island
programme.desc: We'll whisk you to an island where dragons still roam. Deep in the remote basin of the Pacific Ocean, Komodo Island is home to the largest living lizard on the planet. A mythical beast with scales, a long tail and hooked claws, the Komodo dragon fights every day for supremacy and territory. But this deadly predator is also clinging to survival; only around 5,000 of these dragons still exist.

programme.title: Freaks & Creeps E1
programme.desc: Lucy heads off to the rainforests of Borneo where countless strange creatures live. Her goal is get up close with the giant-nosed proboscis monkey. Dr. Pol and Charles start the day tending to a fair pig, whose future isn't looking so fair after all. Will Dr. Pol be able to get this prolapsed show pig back in shape? Across town, Dr. Emily's up to bat, with a cow named Toro - who's abdominal hernia seems to be more than a hiccup on the road to winning the blue ribbon. Now it's Dr. Brenda's turn - there are two horn-y things on the heads of steers, Big Ron and Hannah, preventing them from getting fair-side. When the gates open and the animals come rolling in - Doc Pol's the man the Isabella County Fair looks to, to make sure all of the 4H animals are healthy and ready to show. programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E3
programme.desc: The staff of Pol Vet Services has one head-scratcher after another, from the peculiar to the downright bizarre. With over 19,000 clients, it's only a matter of time before the vets are presented with a unique case that they've never seen before. Dr. Pol leads the charge into uncharted territory. He devises a way to noninvasively remove penile carcinomas threatening a beloved horse, and advises a client on how to best treat her duck whose penis has prolapsed. Dr. Brenda also has her hands full with a herniated pig, and a beagle that has a brain-shaped vaginal polyp. Not to be outdone, Dr. Emily, the newest vet at PVS, completes her 'first flip and stitch' LDA treatment on a dairy cow, treats a tongue-twisted horse, and delivers a deformed calf with no anus. All in a days work at Pol Vet Services!

A violent traitor rises in the rotten ranks, challenging the selfish princess and bringing an end to Mmamotse's rule. The Makulu Pack make one last stand as the battle for supremacy begins, but with the hyenas gone, it's up to Sega to lead the Matahta Pride to victory.

These rays are said to grow to the size of small trucks. If true, this would be the largest fresh water fish ever.

programme.title: Border Security

programme.title: Border Security
programme.desc: Petugas menemukan sepaket ganja di dalam celana seorang pria di Australia. Seorang penumpang wanita membawa ikan dalam jumlah besar di tasnya. Sebuah paket dari India berisi tas-tas wanita yang penuh dengan narkoba.

programme.title: Ghost Hunters
programme.desc: Ghost Hunters membantu orang-orang yang menghadapi fenomena supernatural dengan melibatkan ahli forensik, catatan sejarah dan teknologi paling inovatif yang tersedia.

programme.title: Live PD: Patrol
programme.desc: Ikuti tayangan mendebarkan saat departemen kepolisian beraksi: seorang pecandu narkoba yang hidup kembali di Carolina Selatan, anjing yang menggigit pencuri di Florida, dan penggunaan alat kejut listrik di Illinois.

programme.title: Live PD: Patrol
programme.desc: Ikuti tayangan mendebarkan saat departemen kepolisian beraksi, seperti penyerangan seorang polisi di Texas, baku tembak di Arizona, dan aksi kekerasan dalam rumah tangga di Carolina Selatan.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: Ikuti bagaimana para dektektif menyelidiki sejumlah kasus pembunuhan dengan menelusuri 48 jam pertama dari investigasi mereka kala mereka mengumpulkan petunjuk, bukti dan wawancara dengan para tersangka utama.

programme.title: Leah R.: Scientology
programme.desc: Scientology telah membeli sejumlah gedung besar untuk digunakan sebagai gereja yang dikenal dengan sebutan Ideal Org. Pihak gereja mengklaim bahwa hal itu menandakan perkembangan pesat dari ajaran Scientology.

programme.title: Cults And Extreme Belief
programme.desc: Pengikut FLDS seperti Norma Richter harus membela diri mereka sendiri saat pemimpin mereka, Warren Jeffs, dihukum atas tindakan kekerasan seksual terhadap anak.

programme.title: Escaping Polygamy
programme.desc: Raymond Jeffs, putra Warren Jeffs, meminta bantuan untuk mengeluarkan saudaranya, Ishak, keluar dari sekte tersebut. Mattie, seorang wanita yang melarikan diri dari FLDS, bertemu kembali dengan ibunya.

programme.title: My Crazy Ex
programme.desc: Ikuti kisah-kisah nyata tentang cinta yang awalnya penuh kebahagiaan dan perasaan berbunga-bunga namun berubah drastis tak terkendali hingga akhirnya pasangan-pasangan ini bertekad untuk mengakhiri hubungan mereka.

programme.title: Babies Behind Bars
programme.desc: Jeanie melahirkan secara prematur dan harus dilarikan ke RS. Brandi bertemu dengan orang yang mengadukannya dan membuatnya berada dalam masalah. Ibu Stephanie ingin merawat bayinya, Abigail.

programme.title: Live PD: Patrol
programme.desc: Ikuti tayangan mendebarkan saat departemen kepolisian beraksi. Pada episode kali ini, ikuti perdagangan manusia di Arizona, keributan yang disebabkan oleh narkoba di Texas, dan pengejaran ke wilayah gurun di Utah.

programme.title: Undercover Asia
programme.desc: Di Tiongkok, tingkat perceraian meningkat hampir dua kali lipat selama 10 tahun terakhir. Makin banyaknya pria menikah yang menjalin hubungan dengan wanita lain meningkatkan profesi jasa pelacak pasangan selingkuh.
